  <p>During 3Q20, the construction industry operated without major setbacks after being labeled as an
    "essential" activity towards the end of last quarter, which in turn was reflected in the value of
    the production of construction companies, which from June to July recorded an increase of 1.1%.</p>

  <p>Likewise, the housing institutes commitment to strengthening the industry continued to reflect by means
    of their credit granting schemes for acquisition of new housing, since, in the case of Infonavit,
    it extended its granting goal of "Unamos Creditos" program to 48 thousand credits (vs. the initial goal
    of 14 thousand); while Fovissste announced that it will grant 2,352 additional credits through it
    "Tu casa te espera" program during the remainder of the year.</p>

